# Cursor rules entry

Use **`.ai/`** as the modular instruction system. Start here:

| Path | Responsibility |
|------|----------------|
| `.ai/core/refactor-policy.md` | **Canonical** frozen UI/behaviour/API vs allowed safe refactors |
| `.ai/core/rules.md` | Cross-cutting engineering habits (orchestration, extraction) |
| `.ai/projects/merchant-dashboard.md` | This product: merchant dashboard, **sidebar modules**, stack |
| **`design-guidelines/`** (root) | **UMP visual system** — `OVERVIEW.md` + `rules/**/*.mdc` (portable; copy folder to other products) |
| `.ai/projects/ump-design-guidelines.md` | **Stub** → points at `design-guidelines/` |
| `.ai/skills/build-dashboard-module.md` | Patterns for **any** sidebar module (overview, data, actions, ops, detail) |
| `.ai/prompts/safe-restructure.md` | Pasteable prompt: safe refactors only |
| `.ai/prompts/concept-guidelines.md` | Product framing: clarity, workflow, density — **no** redesign-by-default |

## Enforcement

Work that touches UI or behaviour: follow **`.ai/core/refactor-policy.md`**. Do not restate exceptions here.

## Product code guard

Do **not** modify `src/` when the task is limited to instruction / tooling / `.cursor` / `.ai` layout only.

## Design tokens & components

**Granular `.mdc` specs** live under **`design-guidelines/rules/`** (same pack as `OVERVIEW.md`). Optional Cursor router: **`.cursor/rules/design-guidelines.mdc`**. Use for **explicit** design/token work; they do not override the refactor policy.
